<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CULVER CITY; ARMED 
ROBBERY SUSPECT SHOT TO DEATH BY POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Culver City police shot and killed an armed robbery suspect Monday afternoon 
after he fled from the Fox Hills Mall to an area near Slauson Avenue and the 
Marina Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect, an unidentified man about 30 years old, was wielding a sawed-off 
rifle and was believed to have robbed two stores in the area, investigators 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The first robbery occurred at 12:40 .m. at a Wherehouse record store at 5577 
Sepulveda Blvd. An hour later, the J.C. Penney store in the Fox Hills Mall also 
was robbed and security guards chased the suspect from the store. Authorities 
said the man stole music cassettes from the Wherehouse and clothing from J.C. 
Penney. 
</P>
<P>
 Soon after the man fled, two Culver City police officers found him hiding the 
bushes along the Marina Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the man fired one round at the officers and they returned fire, 
killing him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
