<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 19 
ARRESTED IN CRACKDOWN ON ALLEGED GAMBLING RING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nineteen people were arrested when detectives moved in on what they 
characterized as one of the largest horse and sports gambling rings in the Los 
Angeles area, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The illegal betting operation operated in several Southland communities and 
did millions of dollars in business weekly, said Los Angeles Police Department 
spokesman Rigo Romero. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives culminated the 14-week investigation Sunday when they served 
warrants at 15 locations in Los Angeles, Inglewood, El Segundo, Downey, Anaheim 
Hills, Monterey Park, Arcadia, San Gabriel and Palm Desert, Romero said.  
</P>
<P>
 "This was the largest horse and bookmaking operation that Administrative Vice 
Division detectives have encountered in many years," Romero said.  
</P>
<P>
 Detectives estimated that the operation handled bets for more than 400 
gamblers, "doing a gross betting volume of several million dollars per week," 
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
