<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 3 
AREA EDUCATORS HONORED BY NATIONAL FOUNDATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Los Angeles County educators and an Orange County school principal 
received $25,000 apiece recently as 1994 Milken Family Foundation National 
Educator Award recipients.  
</P>
<P>
 The education excellence awards were presented last week.A banquet in honor of 
the winners will be held sometime this winter. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Bruesch, a sixth-grade teacher at Willard Elementary School in Rosemead 
and mayor of the city, has 25 years experience as an educator. He was 
recognized for developing many of his own instructional programs and curriculum 
materials.  
</P>
<P>
 Victoria Fisher, principal of Rorimer Elementary School in Rowland Heights, 
has worked throughout her career to give underprivileged students a chance to 
fulfill their potential. Gene Bedley, principal of El Camino Real School in 
Orange County, has 20 years on the job. He received the award for his ability 
to focus on and develop children's self-esteem. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 105 awards were given nationally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
