<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 20th Century Industries, a Woodland Hills insurance company that has been hard 
hit by claims from the January Northridge earthquake, announced that the 
executive responsible for overseeing all claims operations for the company is 
retiring Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Group Vice President Paul Castellani had been an officer of the company since 
1983. 
</P>
