<HEADLINE>
<P>
NURSE SAYS HE'S NOT GUILTY OF RAPING PATIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A nurse pleaded not guilty Monday to charges that he raped five women while 
they were under sedation in a hospital's surgical recovery room. 
</P>
<P>
 Circuit Judge John Thurman set a pretrial hearing date of Dec. 5 for Bruce 
Alan Young and entered an order forbidding his accusers to discuss the case 
with each other. 
</P>
<P>
 Young, 45, a registered nurse at Citrus Memorial Hospital since 1990, stood 
shackled hand and foot before the judge. His attorney, William Lackay, wanted 
Thurman to prohibit the accusers from discussing the case with anybody at all, 
but prosecutors protested and the judge narrowed the scope of the request. 
</P>
<P>
 Young has been held under $100,000 bond at the Citrus County Jail since his 
arrest Oct. 3 after another nurse reported seeing him atop a 15-year-old 
anesthetized patient. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said he told them he targeted the unconscious teen-ager because she was 
"helpless and pretty." 
</P>
