<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY: VENTURA; 2 MEN HELD, 2 SOUGHT IN ASSAULT AT PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura police officers have arrested two men and are searching for two others 
in connection with an assault on a 25-year-old Ventura resident, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Guadalupe Rodriguez, suffered a cut to his right eye that required 
stitches, Ventura Police Officer Ray Romero said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the trouble began at a party Sunday night on Mission Street when 
one of the suspects, Braulio Garcia, tried to run over his cousin, Rodriguez, 
with a car. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez ran after Garcia and caught up with him at Park Row Avenue and Olive 
Street, police said. Rodriguez was then knocked down and kicked in the face. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said three other men are suspected of involvement in the assault: 
19-year-old Jose Cruz and 34-year-old Augustine Munoz, who are both in Ventura 
County Jail, and Guadalupe Munoz. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are still trying to locate Garcia and Guadalupe Munoz, Romero said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cruz and Augustine Munoz are scheduled to be arraigned today at 1:30 p.m. in 
Ventura County Municipal Court. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
