<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY: CAMARILLO; CITY PLANS ROUNDUP OF TOXIC WASTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Camarillo residents this week will begin receiving yellow notices announcing 
the city's annual toxic waste roundup scheduled Nov. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, designed to help residents dispose of such materials as paint, 
cleaning solutions, batteries and used motor oil, will be conducted on an 
appointment-only basis. 
</P>
<P>
 Until Nov. 11, residents can call a hot line and leave their name, address and 
a requested appointment time to drop off their household toxic materials. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will then mail residents confirmation cards with their appointment 
times and an address for the location of the roundup.  
</P>
<P>
 Other materials that will be accepted at the roundup include pesticides, weed 
killers, acids, pool chemicals, fertilizers, auto and furniture polish and 
fluorescent light tubes. 
</P>
<P>
 Medical, business and commercial wastes, explosives, smoke alarms, propane 
tanks and gas cylinders will not be accepted. 
</P>
<P>
 To make an appointment for the roundup, call 388-5396. For more information on 
what will and will not be accepted, call the city's community services 
department at 388-5380. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
