<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY: CAMARILLO; SEMINARS TO ASSIST FIRST-TIME INVESTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to help first-time investors make better decisions with their 
finances, the Camarillo Chamber of Commerce will sponsor three seminars 
starting next month, officials announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminars, which are being co-sponsored with Edward D. Jones & Co., will be 
held Nov. 17, Dec. 1 and Dec. 8 from 5:30 to 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Carole Nordahl, the chamber's executive director, said the seminars will cover 
money management, fixed-income investments, growth investments, mutual funds 
and annuities. 
</P>
<P>
 Other topics include retirement planning, life insurance and personal 
investment planning. 
</P>
<P>
 The sessions are free to members of the chamber and are $25 per session for 
non-members. Non-members may apply part of the fees toward charter memberships. 
A light meal will be served. For more information on the seminars, call the 
chamber at 484-4383. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
