<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES ; NEIL F. UNDERWOOD; FARMING FAMILY DESCENDANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Neil F. Underwood, 73, a longtime Camarillo resident and descendant of one of 
Ventura County's original farming families, died Saturday after a long illness. 
He was 73. 
</P>
<P>
 Underwood grew lemons and other crops in the Camarillo area until his 
retirement in 1984. He was a member of the Pleasant Valley Baptist Church, 
which was founded by his great grandparents, John and Rebecca Mahan, who 
settled in Camarillo in the late 1860s. 
</P>
<P>
 He also was an active member in the Camarillo Lions Club and in the Southern 
California Yachting Assn. He served as commodore of the Channel Islands Yacht 
Club in Oxnard in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
 Underwood is survived by his wife, Norma; his brother, Richard of Somis; and 
three daughters, a son and nine grandchildren. Arrangements are being handled 
by Pierce Brothers Griffin Mortuary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
