<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; UCLA; LOOKING AHEAD, BRUINS TRY RECRUITING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM HODGES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a victory over Stanford that ended a six-game losing streak, UCLA has a 
week off, with practices scheduled today, Wednesday and Thursday and recruiting 
all week. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA assistants scattered Monday to take a look at high school prospects and 
were to meet today.Some might leave again after that because Coach Terry 
Donahue is trying to simultaneously conduct a week of practice and recruiting. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins begin preparation in earnest on Monday for the Arizona State game 
Nov. 12 at Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Left guard James Christensen suffered a sprained ligament in his left knee in 
Saturday's game against Stanford. He has been hobbled by a partially torn 
ligament in the same knee that forced him to miss three games and play only 
part of another. 
</P>
<P>
 They are different ligaments. 
</P>
<P>
 He missed the final nine regular season games and the Rose Bowl last season 
because of ligament problems in the same knee and was granted a medical 
hardship redshirt season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 After having interception problems during the losing streak, quarterback Wayne 
Cook has gone three consecutive games without throwing one. During that time, 
Cook has completed 52 of 90 passes for 811 yards and five touchdowns. JIM 
HODGES 
</P>
