<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; NO. 1 ARTISTS END PERFECT LEAGUE RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Beach, the top-ranked team in Orange County, beat Estancia, 12-6, in 
the final Pacific Coast League girls' tennis match Monday at Estancia. 
</P>
<P>
 Palos Verdes Peninsula, the top-ranked team in Division I, was the only team 
to beat the Artists (19-1, 10-0), the top-ranked team in Division II. 
</P>
<P>
 Amanda Hastings-Phillips swept her sets for the Artists, 6-0, 6-1, 6-1. In 
doubles, Michelle Bray and Sarah Cohen swept, 6-1, 6-1, 6-0, for Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Pacific Coast League match: 
</P>
<P>
 University 15, Aliso Niguel 3 -- Mariko Takano swept her sets, 6-1, 6-0, 6-0, 
to give University (10-5, 8-2) the victory and a second-place finish in league. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 13, Woodbridge 5 -- Corona del Mar (16-4), the third-ranked 
team in Orange County, finished league 10-0. Woodbridge is ranked fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 16, El Toro 2 -- Katie Canright swept in singles, 6-0, 6-0, 
6-0, for visiting Newport Harbor (9-6, 6-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 14, Huntington Beach 4 -- Edison (12-6, 8-2) won all nine doubles sets 
and finished second in league behind Los Alamitos. 
</P>
