<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: MARINA'S ROBBINS COMMITS TO PLAY BASKETBALL AT OREGON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shandy Robbins, a senior forward at Marina, said Monday she has made an oral 
commitment to attend Oregon on a basketball scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
 Robbins averaged 17 points and 12 rebounds for Marina, which tied for the 
Sunset League title with Ocean View.She also made the Times' All-Orange County 
team. 
</P>
<P>
 Robbins, who stands nearly 6 feet 1, visited Oregon last weekend and said she 
was impressed with almost everything. 
</P>
<P>
 "It fit all my needs," she said. "I really liked the campus, the team was 
great, and I liked the coaching staff as well. It's a big school and that's 
important because I like to be around a lot of people." 
</P>
<P>
 Robbins also took trips to Pepperdine, Loyola Marymount and UC Santa Barbara. 
STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
