<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAPMAN MISSES SOCCER PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Chapman men's and women's soccer teams received bad news from the NCAA 
Sunday night: Neither team was picked to play in the Division III playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chapman women (12-6) lost to UC San Diego, 3-2, Sunday, which likely ended 
the Panthers' chances of being picked.San Diego (11-0-3) was the only team from 
California to get a playoff spot. 
</P>
<P>
 The Panther men's team beat Division II Cal State Dominguez Hills, 2-0, 
Sunday. Chapman Coach Gregg Murphy believed Chapman's strength of schedule 
would help earn it the bid despite a 10-4-3 record. 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman beat Division I UC Santa Barbara and was 1-1-1 in games against 
Division II opponents. UC San Diego (11-6-1) and Claremont-Mudd (15-2-1), teams 
that Chapman tied, each received playoff berths. 
</P>
<P>
 "Claremont had a better record than us, but their schedule wasn't nearly as 
strong," Murphy said. 
</P>
<P>
 Both Chapman teams will complete their seasons by playing host to Cal Poly 
Pomona today. MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</TEXT>
