<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: BIOPOOL INTERNATIONAL'S PROFITS UP IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Biopool International Inc., a Ventura-based maker of medical test kits, 
reported vastly improved profits in the third quarter that ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 Earnings in the latest quarter surged to $159,371, up from $32,629 in the same 
quarter a year earlier.Sales jumped 32% to $1.36 million from $1.03 million in 
the third quarter a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine-month period, Biopool reported earnings of $549,198 on sales of 
$4.06 million, compared to year-earlier profit of $161,736 on revenue of $3.20 
million. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael D. Bick, chief executive of the company, attributed the improved 
results to sales and marketing efforts that increased the company's market 
share, as well as new products. During the third quarter, the company received 
approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration to sell a num ber of new 
products, including additions to the company's line of kits used to test for 
drug abuse. 
</P>
