<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: HUNTWAY REPORTS DECLINE IN PROFIT FOR 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntway Partners L.P., a Newhall-based producer of liquid asphalt from crude 
oil, reported a sharp drop in third-quarter earnings and revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The 94% decline in profit, to $203,000 in the quarter that ended Sept. 30 from 
$3.35 million a year earlier, came as crude oil processing costs increased and 
prices for Huntway's products fell. Revenue decreased 19%, to $23.9 million 
from $29.5 million, largely due to the closure of its Arizona refinery. 
</P>
<P>
 In the recent nine-month period, Huntway narrowed its loss to $1.83 million, 
while its revenue fell 30%, to $56.8 million. In the same period a year before, 
it lost $19.8 million on $80.7 million in revenue. 
</P>
