 Syncor International Corp., a Chatsworth-based pharmacy services network, said 
it lost $1.1 million for the third quarter ended Sept. 30, compared to earnings 
of $3 million in the same period a year earlier. The loss was on a 35% increase 
in revenue to $81.6 million from $60.4 million in the third quarter last year. 
</P>
