decline from $8.8 million earned in the same period last year. Revenues for the 
period were $238.3 million, up 33% from $179.8 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said its results for the nine months were affected by price cuts 
it made earlier this year. The cuts failed to bring about a projected increase 
in sales. Also, a flat market for nuclear medicine services -- Syncor's core 
business -- and pressure to reduce costs in health care have hurt Syncor's 
margins, despite a strategic alliance struck earlier this year with DuPont Co. 
and Merck & Co. that opened new areas of business, the company said. 
