<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: REXHALL INDUSTRIES PROFITS RISE 75% IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rexhall Industries Inc., a Santa Clarita builder of mobile homes, said its 
earnings for the third quarter that ended Sept. 30 were $513,000, up 75% from 
$293,000 in the same quarter a year earlier.Sales for the third quarter were 
$14.02 million, up 80% from $7.8 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For its nine-month period, the company posted earnings of $1.57 million, more 
than double the $741,000 in earnings reported in the first nine months of 1993. 
The gain was on a 71% revenue surge to $35.9 million from $20.96 million in the 
first nine months of last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results for all three quarters to the improving 
local economy and to expansion of its dealership network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
