<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: FORMER NEWSPAPER BUILDING IS FOR SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The building that formerly housed the Oxnard Press Courier is for sale. 
</P>
<P>
 CB Commercial Real Estate's Ventura office is offering the newspaper's plant 
on Oxnard's West 9th Street at an asking price of $2.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The 52,000-square-foot building is owned by Thomson Newspapers, which folded 
the Press Courier last June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
