<P>
COMPANY TOWN; CAP CITIES, IMAX JOIN IN VENTURE FOR GIANT-SCREEN MOTION PICTURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capital Cities/ABC Inc. and Imax Corp. said Monday they have formed a joint 
venture to make giant-screen motion pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 The agreement calls for Imax to distribute the films, which would be jointly 
financed by the two companies.There are currently 115 Imax theaters in 18 
countries. About 35 more are scheduled to open in the next few years. 
</P>
<P>
 The venture will focus on topics such as natural history and space 
exploration, which the companies said have a broader appeal than traditional 
Imax films on educational and travel-related subjects. 
</P>
<P>
 The joint venture will also explore projects related to the ABC television 
network's coverage of news and sports and look into videocassette, CD-ROM and 
multimedia applications. 
</P>
<P>
 Toronto-based Imax, founded in 1967, specializes in giant-screen and motion 
simulator films. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the ABC-TV network, Cap Cities operates eight television 
stations, the ABC radio network and 19 radio stations. The New York-based 
company also produces programming for cable television. 
</P>
