<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; COLLEGE OFFERS SERVICES FOR NATURALIZATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A one-stop processing center for immigrants who want to become naturalized 
citizens has opened at Rancho Santiago College in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the services offered are application workshops, fingerprinting and 
photos.A written citizenship test approved by the Immigration and 
Naturalization Service is administered on the second Saturday of the month. 
</P>
<P>
 Legalization and civics classes required for citizenship, along with 
English-language courses, are offered by the college at various sites in Santa 
Ana. There is no fee. 
</P>
<P>
 The Citizenship Center is in Room E-109N of the campus Centennial Education 
Center, at 2900 W. Edinger Ave. Orientation sessions are from 1 to 2:30 p.m. 
Tuesdays and 6 to 7:30 p.m. Thursdays in Room A-107 at the Centennial Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Regular operating hours for the Citizenship Center are 4 to 8 p.m. Tuesdays, 
Wednesdays and Thursdays. The facility is open at other times by appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 Additional information is available by calling the college at (714) 564-5060. 
ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
