<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CYPRESS; STABBING DEATH OF TEEN INVESTIGATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police on Monday were probing the fatal stabbing of an Anaheim teen-ager 
during a fight in a parking lot Sunday on Ball Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddie Alexander Young, 18, ran bleeding for a block before collapsing in front 
of a business, Police Lt. Jim Weuve said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they had no suspects and it was not known what the fight was 
about. 
</P>
<P>
 Some witnesses said they saw the fight but not the stabbing, which took place 
about 5:30 p.m. at a business complex in the 6200 block, Weuve said. The 
attacker fled on foot, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 A bystander called 911 and police officers found Young bleeding heavily. 
Paramedics provided treatment, but Young was pronounced dead at Los Alamitos 
Medical Center, Weuve said. KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
