<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACCIDENTAL SHOOTING VICTIM DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 24 year-old man who accidentally shot himself in the head while handling a 
gun died Monday of his wound, according to the Orange County coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Ortiz Mejia of Garden Grove had been on life-support systems since 
Sunday night, when police found him at his home in the 13000 block of Blackbird 
Street, according to Garden Grove police. 
</P>
<P>
 Mejia was in his living room just before 11 p.m., handling a small-caliber, 
semi-automatic handgun, when witnesses told police they heard a shot and saw 
him fall over, according to Lt. John Woods. 
</P>
<P>
 An autopsy is scheduled for today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
