<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: ENCINO; CHAMBER TO HONOR 8 PUBLIC EMPLOYEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Encino Chamber of Commerce will hold its second annual Community Service 
Awards luncheon Nov. 10 to thank eight individuals -- from police officers to 
letter carriers -- who perform often thankless jobs. 
</P>
<P>
 "Their dedication and commitment is what makes this a great place to live and 
work," said chamber President Steve Getzoff."We want to take a few minutes to 
honor them for everything they give us." 
</P>
<P>
 Among the honorees at this year's ceremony will be Frank Bush of the Los 
Angeles Department of Building and Safety. 
</P>
<P>
 "We usually don't do building and safety, but this gentleman went above and 
beyond the call of duty after the (Northridge) earthquake," said Jan Sobel, 
chamber executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 Others to be recognized at the luncheon are: Officer Sandy Cline and Detective 
Craig Rhudy of the Los Angeles Police Department's Van Nuys Division, Officer 
John Futrell and Senior Lead Officer Victor Monroe of the LAPD's West Valley 
Division, engineer Patrick Leddy and Firefighter/Lead Paramedic Dennis Archie 
of the Los Angeles Fire Department, and letter carrier Linda McGaha of the U. 
S. Postal Service. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is welcome at the luncheon, to be held at 11:30 a.m. at the Braemar 
Country Club, 4001 Reseda Blvd., Tarzana. The cost is $15 for chamber members 
and $18 for non-members. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations or more information, call the Encino Chamber of Commerce at 
(818) 789-4711. ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</TEXT>
