BRIEFCASE: RETAIL; WESTMINSTER MALL LOOKING FORWARD TO PROSPEROUS SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westminster Mall, in a news release dated Monday, quotes economists as 
predicting a "prosperous Christmas for Orange County retailers." 
</P>
<P>
 According to Westminster Mall, an economist with KeyCorp, an Albany, 
N.Y.-based banking company, predicts that Orange County consumers will spend 
between 7% and 10% more than they did during last year's holiday season.  
</P>
<P>
 What will that buy? Westminster Mall's marketing director, Stephanie Greene, 
is betting that consumers will be buying luxury personal items, large-screen 
televisions, toys and high-tech electronics products. 
