<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOD FOR THOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The way to a football team might be through the club president's stomach. 
</P>
<P>
 In their 4 1/2-hour meeting in Los Angeles last month, former Missouri Sen. 
Thomas Eagleton, who is heading St. Louis' efforts to land an NFL team, said 
Rams President John Shaw seemed a bit concerned about the caliber of 
restaurants in St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
 "Mr. Shaw asked me if St. Louis was a gourmet town, and I said, 'Well, we have 
some nice restaurants,' " Eagleton said. "Then he said, 'Tell me, is it like 
San Francisco?' Well, no. He said, 'How about New Orleans?' 
</P>
<P>
 "I said, 'Well, in some respects, we're a raucous Des Moines!' " MIKE 
DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</TEXT>
