<LENGTH>
<P>
130 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCC COACH TRANI JUMPS TO GAUCHOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nick Trani, the softball coach at Orange Coast the last six seasons, is 
leaving to take the same position at Saddleback, he said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Trani hopes to eventually get a full-time teaching position at Saddleback.He 
worked at OCC as a walk-on, teaching only the softball class. He will teach 
three classes at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm looking forward to the challenge," Trani said. "It's a great area for 
talent and the administration is excited about the program." 
</P>
<P>
 Trani had a 180-92 mark at OCC, including reaching the State tournament three 
of the last four seasons. His 1992 team won the Orange Empire Conference title. 
</P>
<P>
 Trani will be joined by his OCC assistants Jesse Sims and John Campbell. 
</P>
<P>
 "The hardest part was telling the players (at OCC)," Trani said. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
