<HEADLINE>
<P>
BLYLEVEN QUITS AS ANGEL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bert Blyleven, who was hired in October to be the Angels' Class A pitching 
coach at Cedar Rapids, abruptly resigned and today will become the director of 
sports ministry at his church. 
</P>
<P>
 "This just came up," Blyleven said. "I know the Angels were surprised, but 
this is God's way of telling me I shouldn't leave." 
</P>
<P>
 Blyleven said he will work with the Crystal Cathedral's youth and organize 
recreational sports. 
</P>
<P>
 "I still eventually want to manage in the minor leagues, and one day go to the 
major league level but not now," Blyleven said. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
